uable source for understanding economic thought in pre-modern Europe, but also a fertile resource for scholars of law, economics, and philosophy in medieval Europe and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEconomicsxEarly works to 1800xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aEconomicsxMoral and ethical aspectsvEarly works to 1800. 0aLaw, Medieval. 0aNatural lawvEarly works to 1800. 0aNatural lawxEarly works to 1800. 0aPhilosophy, Medieval. 0aPrescription (Law)vEarly works to 1800. 0aPrescription (Law)xEarly works to 1800. 0aRestitutionvEarly works to 1800. 0aRestitutionxEarly works to 1800. 0aTheologyxHistoryxMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aTheologyxHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aUsuryvEarly works to 1800. 0aUsuryxEarly works to 1800. 7aLAW / Legal History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066595640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269568940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442695689423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442695689.jpg  a978-3-11-066595-6  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles